    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a type of pâte de verre that is characterized by being especially translucent. It was developed by Gabriel Argy-Rousseau, a famous Art-Deco glass designer of the 1920s and 1930s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
